      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "a20441ca4a888018",
      "text": "The vocabulary we use is drawn from our collective beliefs, values and school philosophies. For the staff at Griffin, the words, phrases and terms we choose to use when naming our processes, practices and artefacts reminds us about the purpose behind what we do and why we do it. When we decide on terms that we want to use, we deliberately choose words that show worth and reflect our culture. We carefully select shared language for people, processes, routines, buildings and school areas. For us, labels are powerful communicators of our beliefs and values."
